    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1956-12-24T17:09:00-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1956-12-24T17:09:00-05:00" n="52"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d52">
                <head>52. Telegram From the <gloss type="from">Department of State</gloss> to the
                        <gloss type="to">Embassy in Saudi Arabia</gloss>
                    <note n="1" type="source" xml:id="d52fn1">Source: Department of State, Central
                        Files, 685.00/12–2456. Top Secret. Drafted by <persName corresp="#p_WF2"
                            >Wilkins</persName> and <persName corresp="#p_BDC1">Bergus</persName>
                        and approved by <persName corresp="#p_RWM1">Rountree</persName> who signed
                        for <persName corresp="#p_HHJ1">Hoover</persName>. Repeated to Amman,
                        Baghdad, Cairo, Damascus, and London.</note>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="italic">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1956-12-24T17:09:00-05:00">
                            <hi rend="italic">December 24, 1956—5:09 p.m.</hi>
                        </date>
                    </dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>451. <gloss target="#t_Embtel1">Embtel</gloss> 335.<note n="2" xml:id="d52fn2"
                        >See <ref target="#d252fn4">footnote 4, Document 252</ref>.</note> You
                    should convey to King <persName corresp="#p_EMJSD1">Saud</persName> appreciation
                    for his timely message to King <persName corresp="#p_Hussein1"
                        >Hussein</persName> and belief that exercise of King <persName
                        corresp="#p_EMJSD1">Saud</persName>’s influence should be continued in Amman
                    and that we should both make effective use of resources at our command in
                    suitable ways to assist Jordan. US for example has been aiding <pb facs="0109"
                        n="77" xml:id="pg_77"/> Jordan for some years through provision of some $8
                    million annually in technical assistance and economic development and some $17.5
                    million annually in contributions for Arab refugees over half of whom are in
                    Jordan. King <persName corresp="#p_EMJSD1">Saud</persName>’s comments as to
                    effective use of Saudi Arabia resources for suitable assistance to Jordan would
                    be helpful. In discussing this matter with King <persName corresp="#p_EMJSD1"
                        >Saud</persName> and other <gloss target="#t_SAG1">SAG</gloss> officials and
                    in obtaining their comments you may as you think desirable inform them of
                    substance of accompanying <gloss target="#t_Deptel1">Deptel</gloss> to
                        Amman<note n="3" xml:id="d52fn3">
                        <ref target="#d53">
                            <hi rend="italic">Infra.</hi>
                        </ref>
                    </note> on this subject.</p>
                <p>. . . . . . .</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <persName corresp="#p_DJF1">
                            <hi rend="strong">Dulles</hi>
                        </persName>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
